+{"id":"wa-29cb","title":"zstd compression bypass — skip compression on local Unix socket","description":"## Goal
Skip zstd compression on local Unix socket connections to the mux server, eliminating unnecessary CPU overhead for data that never leaves the machine.

## Background & Motivation
WezTerm's mux protocol applies zstd compression to ALL PDU payloads, including traffic over local Unix sockets. This is useful for remote SSH connections but pure waste for local connections:
- Compression/decompression burns CPU cycles on every request/response
- Local Unix socket transfers are already fast (kernel memory copy, no network)
- With 250+ requests/second under 50-pane load, this is significant overhead

## Technical Design

### Detection
Detect local vs remote connection based on socket type:
```rust
fn is_local_socket(path: &Path) -> bool {
    // Unix domain sockets are always local
    path.exists() && path.to_string_lossy().contains("wezterm-mux")
}
```

### Bypass Implementation
In the vendored mux client (mux_client.rs), conditionally skip zstd:
```rust
impl DirectMuxClient {
    fn encode_pdu(&self, pdu: &Pdu) -> Vec<u8> {
        let raw = pdu.serialize();
        if self.is_local {
            raw  // No compression for local sockets
        } else {
            zstd::encode_all(&raw[..], self.compression_level).unwrap()
        }
    }
}
```

### Protocol Negotiation
The codec version handshake already includes compression capability flags. For local connections, negotiate no-compression mode. This requires a FrankenTerm fork change to the mux server to accept uncompressed PDUs when the client indicates local mode.

### Fallback
If the server doesn't support no-compression mode (upstream WezTerm), fall back to zstd as before. This ensures backward compatibility during the transition.

## Existing Code References
- vendored/mux_client.rs: PDU encode/decode with zstd
- WezTerm source: codec.rs, DecodedPdu, zstd integration
- wire_protocol.rs: PROTOCOL_VERSION negotiation

## Expected Impact
- 5-10% CPU reduction for capture-heavy workloads
- Lower latency per PDU (skip compression/decompression)
- Most impactful when combined with connection pool (bd-41w) — persistent connections amortize negotiation

## Configuration
```toml
[mux_pool]
compression = "auto"  # "auto" | "always" | "never"
# auto: skip compression for local sockets, compress for remote
```

## Dependencies
- Requires FrankenTerm fork (mux server must accept uncompressed local PDUs)
- Enhanced by bd-41w (persistent connections reduce per-connection overhead)

## Acceptance Criteria
- Local connections bypass zstd compression
- Remote connections still use zstd
- Protocol negotiation handles mixed environments
- Fallback to compressed mode for upstream WezTerm compatibility
- Benchmark: measure CPU reduction for 50-pane capture workload

